            <fr:addr type="user">frct-0018</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>frct-0018.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The total opposite of a displayed category">The total opposite of a displayed category</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:anchor>2566</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">frct-001I</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>frct-001I.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Total opposite category">Total opposite category</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Construction</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be displayed over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>; we define its <fr:em>total opposite</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E^{\tilde {\mathsf {o}}}]]></fr:tex> displayed over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B^{\mathsf {op}}]]></fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
                <fr:ol><fr:li>An object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E^{\tilde {\mathsf {o}}}_{x}]]></fr:tex> is given by an object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_{x}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Given <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : x \to  y\in  B^{\mathsf {op}}]]></fr:tex>, a displayed morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {x}\xrightarrow [f]{} \bar {y}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E^{\tilde {\mathsf {o}}}]]></fr:tex> is given by a displayed morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {y}\xrightarrow [f]{} \bar {x}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
                <fr:p><fr:strong>Warning.</fr:strong> Do not confuse this construction with the <fr:link href="frct-001Z.xml" title="The opposite of an uncloven fibration" addr="frct-001Z" type="local">opposite fibered category</fr:link>, which produces a displayed category over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> and not <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B^{\mathsf {op}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:anchor>2567</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">frct-001J</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>frct-001J.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="" />
                <fr:taxon>Exercise</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be displayed over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>. Prove that the <fr:link href="frct-000A.xml" title="The total category and its projection" addr="frct-000A" type="local">total category</fr:link>
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\widetilde {E^{\tilde {\mathsf {o}}}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\widetilde {E}\right )\mathclose {}}^{\mathsf {op}}]]></fr:tex>, and its projection functor is
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (p_{E}\right )\mathclose {}}^{\mathsf {op}} : \widetilde {E}^{\mathsf {op}}\to B^{\mathsf {op}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:anchor>2568</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">frct-001K</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>frct-001K.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="" />
                <fr:taxon>Exercise</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be displayed over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:x\to  y\in  B]]></fr:tex>. Prove that a
morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {f}:\bar {x}\xrightarrow [f]{}\bar {y}]]></fr:tex> is cartesian over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> if and only
if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {f}:\bar {y}\xrightarrow [f]{}\bar {x}]]></fr:tex> is cocartesian over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E^{\tilde {\mathsf {o}}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
